Position Details
job Responsibilities
• Develop Drive Test applications which enable engineers of Mobile Operators to ensure radio and application coverage, capacity and quality of complex mobile networks.
• Participate in full software development lifecyle which includes requirements, analysis, design, coding, unit testing, etc as part of agile scrum team
Required Qualifications
Required Qualifications
• Masters / Degree in Engineering or Computer Science
• A few years hands-on experience as an R&D; software developer in a distributed multi-site application development
• Strong in C++/C#/.NET programming languages
• Previous experience as a software developer using C++/C#/.NET in Visual Studio and a MS development environment
• Experience in interfacing with device drivers and mobile handsets.
• Detail orientated and yet very broad in scope
• Proven to be a very fast thinker with strong execution and problem solving skills
• Flexible in working hours due to the time zone differences between the multiple sites
• Able to work independently and in teams
• Experience in Agile scrum and rapid development cycles in a highly dynamic changing business environment is an added advantage
• Demonstrated strong initiative, ownership, communication and teamwork skills - Experience in working with globally diverse teams
